{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-00658/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-00658"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:06:58"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man paces around a room."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-00658","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-00658"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1/7f4f473c-9f48-4e96-ab85-2f216944675f","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T13:56:46.593Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds lingers in the petit salon, pacing the floor. He almost resembles a groom awaiting his bride at their wedding. He cannot see Henrietta until she is fully dressed.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:677.6386861313869,166.67518248175182,208.89416058394158,856.8722627737226"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1/dead7f9e-a077-4c26-a136-c6d358721d4d","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T13:58:08.994Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Set decorator Véronique Melery selected the “classical French Aubusson of an 18th century design” as it “offers a background to the dresses without being too much of a statement” (Burg, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW38464952 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.setdecorators.org/?art=film_decor_features&amp;SHOW=SetDecor_Film_Phantom_Thread\"><u>Set Decore</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:499.70802919708024,986.3978102189781,951.6350364963503,67.54379562043812"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1/089f21f0-df09-4005-bd64-7dffeb6c10fd","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T13:58:26.942Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>While it is difficult to definitively identify the sculpture in the back of the studio, the work appears to evoke motifs associated with the “wounded Amazon,” a classical type that features the legendary race of mythical warrior women in a contrapposto pose with one arm raised above their heads and a chiton falling from the shoulder to expose the breast. This figure, then, could signal elements of feminine strength in combat that mark Reynolds’s relationships with both Alma and Cyril.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1014.8759124087592,105.54744525547446,113.01459854014593,299.4744525547445"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1/20699387-cc33-490d-a8d3-44a87b2cd3f0","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T13:58:46.359Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Sculptures also figured prominently in Cristóbal Balenciaga’s business: “Even the shop windows, decorated by Janine Janey, gave no hint of commerce. Balenciaga forbade the display of merchandise, with the result that Janet created sculptures for them that were in their way as ravishing and original as Balenciaga’s own work” (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>, 95).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00658/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:15.3394160583942,42.416058394160565,177.94160583941604,125.69343065693434"}}}]}]}]}